<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why AE Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Over the weekend I finished ND 3 and now I am looking for my next path for AAs.  Everything (and everyone) seems to say AE Taunt is where I need to go next.  I seem to be the only one that sees limited use for AE Taunt.  My main role as a warrior is as MT for a medium tier part time raiding guild.  We have just started stepping into NToV, we hit WToV and First broods whenever they are up, and PoP so far has been limited to Xanamech and Vhkaziz.  I am in my element when I am the target of a cheal cycle, that is my prefered role.  Since ND and adding more hp/sta items, I have actually been surviving to the end of the battle despite defensive running out or a missed heal.  I keep aggro with little to no problems in these fights, so I have seen very little opportunity where I would need to use AE Taunt...in fact I almost never even need to hit taunt at all.  My thought was that I would be better served to go after CA and CS before AE Taunt, so as to conserve healers mana better.  What I was hoping for was some thoughts from others that already have AE Taunt, as to why I should pick that over the defensive AAs, so as to have a better idea which is better for me.<br>
<br>
<br>
