<br>
For me, AT is a lifesaver. It is great for raids with tank switching, but also for saving that shammy who slows just a little early one time and your taunt fails, or when your chanter is getting a beating trying to get adds locked down.<br>
<br>
<br>
Seriously tho, you can't spend 5 points better than by buying AT taunt. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=strikingone>StrikingOne</A> at: 4/14/03 10:12:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brutultarewmarr>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 1173<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/03 10:54 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~laforman/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why AE Taunt?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Seriously tho, you can't spend 5 points better than by buying AT taunt. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
