<br>
Most common use for me on raids is tank switching.  MA drops, bossmob_01 starts beating on random_squishy_caster_01, taunt fails as usual, I AE Taunt, bossmob_01 is locked on me til he or I die.  <br>
<br>
There's lot more uses for it though:<br>
<br>
- Overpull with no crowd control?  Wait for that first round of heals/debuffs, AE taunt, all mobs are locked on you for most if not all of the fight.<br>
<br>
- Chanter gets 15 resists on slow and taunt isn't doing anything?  AE Taunt and you now have 15 slows worth of aggro...<br>
<br>
- Wipe in progress on a raid?  AE Taunt plus defensive and give your clerics some extra time to camp.<br>
<br>
- Chanter dies on an AE pull?  AE Taunt plus evac...<br>
<br>
Notice most of these scenarios involve crowd control?  AE Taunt is your ONLY reliable way to control mob aggro.  Get it.  You won't regret it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=472195">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
