<br>
Even if your aggro is so completely rock solid that you NEVER lose it (which I doubt with a shovel of harvest...not a slam, just an obvservation), it's still useful for springboarding off aggro of certain classes to put you ahead of the pack.  If your shamans normally die on mobs that are difficult to slow, you can time the taunt to land right as they get summoned and they can walk away, and keep contributing to the raid, rather than contributing to downtime.  There's also the thought that there may be a day when you're NOT first tank in a particular area, and without AETaunt, tank transitions are iffy, at best.  Do you wanna be 5 points away from that ability should the situation arise?<br>
<br>
You can go ahead and get CA/CS if you want, i'm just telling you that damned near every day I play, I save someone's ass with AE Taunt.  That means less downtime, and that means I accomplish more in my day.  Accomplishing more in my day is a good thing, but if you think CA is the way to go for you, by all means, go for it.  CA, with an extra point over what you would have spent in AE taunt, means 5% better avoidance.  AE taunt means that someone else doesn't have to worry about avoidance, and you're doing your job better. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
